      contents:
        "<p>Join ourGlobal Cybersecurity Governance team which is responsible for providing acommon Cybersecurity Regulatory Framework across the Siemens business unitsworldwide.<br><br>We atSiemens are more than employees: We are actively helping to make people's livesa little better every day. Would you like to be a part of that? Then join us.We offer you a high level of practical relevance as well as an opportunity toindividually contribute with your knowledge and your visions around the world.At Siemens CYS you'll be working in the heart of Siemens' corporateCybersecurity team together with the best.<br><br>We makereal what matters. <br><br><strong>This isyour role:</strong><br><br>Thisposition will be a key resource in the development of all aspects of thecompany's Cybersecurity Governance program, with a special focus on developingand maintaining a state-of-the-art cybersecurity policy framework based onInternational legal requirements, consulting Siemens' Units in adopting ourgovernance requirements, as well supporting corporate projects for improvingCybersecurity.<br><br><strong>Essentialfunctions include, but are not limited to:</strong><br><br><ul><li>Leadthe integration of international Cybersecurity Legislation into our Governanceframework by developing and maintaining future-state Cybersecurity policies andcontrol objectives.</li><li>Supportprojects to maintain compliance with regulatory, contractual, and internalrequirements.</li><li>TrainSiemens Cybersecurity Community to understand Siemens Cybersecurity PolicyFramework and international Cybersecurity Legislation.</li><li>Supportand provide advice to Siemens' Units and customers on topics related toCybersecurity governance: e.g. implementation of international standards(ISO27001, IEC 62443, etc.); support during the certification processes; orconsulting on the practical Implementation of governance requirements.</li></ul><br><strong>Use yourskills to move the world forward:</strong><br><br><ul><li>Atleast 4-6 years of experience with Cybersecurity Legislation, governanceframeworks and methodologies.</li><li>Master'sdegree or similar in law.</li><li>Englishfluent proficiency both written and spoken.</li><li>Knowledgeon arising international Cybersecurity legislation (e.g. CRA, GDPR, NIS,NIS2.0, IT SiG 2.0(Germany), Chinese Cybersecurity law, etc.).</li><li>Exceptionalcommunication skills, including the ability to gather relevant data andinformation, actively listen, dialogue freely, verbalize ideas effectively,negotiate tense situations successfully, and manage and resolve conflict.</li><li>Solidknowledge about cybersecurity governance frameworks (ISO, NIST, COBIT, IEC,etc.)</li><li>Excellentteamwork and ability to collaborate with others</li><li>Certificationon ISO27001 and IEC 62443 frameworks, as well as CISA, CISM are a plus.</li></ul><br><strong>This role is open to be hired in Spain or Portugal. Please, submit your CV in English</strong><br><br>Diversity at Siemens is our source for creativityand innovation. Leveraging different types of talent, experience, and culturalbackgrounds helps us to be more competitive and better prepared to successfullyface our society's demand. Therefore, we value candidates who reflect theDiversity we are proud to have in our company<br><br>#LI-DL<br><br><b>Organization:</b> Cybersecurity<br><br><b>Company:</b> Siemens S.A.<br><br><b>Experience Level:</b> Experienced Professional<br><br><b>Full / Part time:</b> Full-time</p>",
