        "<p>If you want to advance your career as a tester, or test automation specialist, you found the right job  We're looking for graduates who want to start their career in software development as testers, for junior testers, for enthusiasts in coding who want to grow.<br><br>As we're starting a new team, we're looking also for more experienced people, up to level of test architect, so if you want to apply and didn't find our other job posts, apply here<br><br>At Siemens Healthineers we develop a software for healthcare. Such software needs quality and the quality needs you and your passion for quality work, personal expertise and career growth. Join us today and if you want to refer your colleagues or friends, you have a unique opportunity to have a say with whom you would work<br><br><strong>Desired skills:</strong><br><br>\u2022 Basic Java, but wants to advance<br><br>\u2022 Basic experience with Selenium<br><br>\u2022 General understanding of HTML, CSS, DOM, JSON, XML, JS<br><br>\u2022 Ideally experience with Azure DevOps<br><br>\u2022 Experience with these or similar tools: IntelliJ, Gradle, PowerShell<br><br>\u2022 Good communication skills<br><br><strong>Language skills:</strong><br><br>\u2022 English - Upper intermediate (B2)<br><br><strong>We offer</strong><br><br>\u2022 Personal development plan, personal career plan, learning materials and platforms access<br><br>\u2022 Work-life balance and well-being focus<br><br>\u2022 Variable and Christmas bonus<br><br>\u2022 Hybrid type of work - combination of telework and work from office<br><br>\u2022 Flexible Working Hours<br><br>\u2022 Bridge days - free extra paid leave 6 days per year<br><br>\u2022 3 sick days per year (no doctor's permit needed)<br><br>\u2022 In case of sickness 100% salary reimbursement 20 days/ year, this includes max. 10 days/ year for of family care<br><br>\u2022 Additional pension plan<br><br>\u2022 300 EUR for regeneration of work force via cafeteria system<br><br>\u2022 Wellbeing program - Psychological, Legal and Financial Counselling<br><br>\u2022 Family care program (subsidy for newborns, maternity leave, kindergartens, summer camps)<br><br>\u2022 Retention program (work anniversary, life anniversary, employee loans)<br><br>\u2022 Training and development program (business and product trainings, e-learning, language courses, soft skills trainings...)<br><br>\u2022 Adjustable standing desk as a standard<br><br>\u2022 Participation on world famous IT conferences like Microsoft IGNITE for best employees<br><br>\u2022 Wide project portfolio in healthcare domain and job rotation within company (Cybersecurity, Artificial ---Intelligence, Healthcare IT services, ...)<br><br><strong>More about us</strong>: https://www.siemens-healthineers.com/sk/development-center <br><br><strong>More about me</strong>: https://www.linkedin.com/in/marekvisnovsky/ https://www.instagram.com/marek_visnovsky/<br><br><strong>Basic wagecomponent (gross) and other rewards</strong> :starting from 1600EUR brutto /month + VAR<em><br><br></em>We arerequired by law to disclose basic wage component (minimum salary) for theadvertised positions. We carefully consider your professional qualificationsand experience in our compensation package and/or when offering you otherpositions.<br><br>Our goal is topay our employee's fairly, with regard to the market situation and we are readyto welcome high-quality candidates in our team.<br><br><b>Organization:</b> Siemens Healthineers<br><br><b>Company:</b> Siemens Healthcare s.r.o.<br><br><b>Experience Level:</b> Early Professional<br><br><b>Full / Part time:</b> Full-time</p>",
