      contents:
        '<p><strong>1</strong><br><br><strong>Job Profile - Sales BA for GBS FIN China</strong><br><br><strong>You will be the Finance Business Partner for Business and Service Lines in the GBS</strong><br><br><strong>operations. This role also provides commercial support to the Management of Business Line</strong><br><br><strong>and Service lines with regard to sales activities.</strong><br><br><strong>Furthermore you provide financial support of operations and support during projects due</strong><br><br><strong>diligence phases as needed.</strong><br><br><strong>Sales BA - Main responsibilities:</strong><br><br><strong>- Together with respective Business Line and Service Line managers to secure orders from</strong><br><br><strong>internal and external customers end-to-end, from bid phase to contract execution.</strong><br><br><strong>- Price and Cost calculation for each standard product of BLs/SLs under aligned cost calculation</strong><br><br><strong>method and pricing strategy.</strong><br><br><strong>- Support contract negotiations with customers and take and are driving the order management</strong><br><br><strong>process.</strong><br><br><strong>- Prepare offer calculations including profitability analysis in relation to the overall business</strong><br><br><strong>case.</strong><br><br><strong>- Handle commercial topics e.g. contract T&amp;C, price calculation for particular project</strong><br><br><strong>- Prepare rationality and bridge analysis (if required).</strong><br><br><strong>- You will be involved in driving forward finance digitalization topics across the organization.</strong><br><br><strong>- Support execution of various support functions, including risk management and compliance,</strong><br><br><strong>business excellence, internal audit, procurement, and others to deliver world class business</strong><br><br><strong>results.</strong><br><br><strong>- You interact cooperatively with all stakeholders both within as well as outside of GBS and</strong><br><br><strong>manage third party relationships as needed.</strong><br><br><strong>- You are willing to assume and complete ad-hoc / special projects and/or other assignments as</strong><br><br><strong>delegated by management.</strong><br><br><strong>Qualifications</strong><br><br><strong>. University degree in Business Administration, Accounting and Finance, CPA and/or MBA</strong><br><br><strong>preferable.</strong><br><br><strong>2</strong><br><br><strong>. You have least 5 years of professional experience in accounting and controlling, combined</strong><br><br><strong>with knowledge in Service/Product/Systems/IT/Software or Shared Services industry.</strong><br><br><strong>. You can demonstrate in-depth business knowledge as well as first-class presentation and</strong><br><br><strong>communication skills.</strong><br><br><strong>. You have experience with commercial bid management, Sales business administration tasks</strong><br><br><strong>and commercial project management.</strong><br><br><strong>. You solve problems proactively and are used to presenting problems with a solution. Ideally,</strong><br><br><strong>you have demonstrated this as member in project groups.</strong><br><br><strong>. You convince with very high analytical competence, very high level of commitment, your</strong><br><br><strong>focus on results, a confident manner and your assertiveness.</strong><br><br><strong>. You are proficient with Microsoft Office applications and have experience with commercial</strong><br><br><strong>SAP applications as well as Siemens-specific tools and solutions.</strong><br><br><strong>. Your fluent Chinese and English skills - spoken and written knowledge - round off your</strong><br><br><strong>profile.</strong><br><br><b>Organization:</b> Global Business Services<br><br><b>Company:</b> Siemens Ltd., China<br><br><b>Experience Level:</b> Mid-level Professional<br><br><b>Full / Part time:</b> Full-time</p>',
