      contents:
        '<p><strong>Job Description</strong><br><br>At Siemens we are always challenging ourselves to build a better future.  We need the most innovative and diverse Digital Minds to develop tomorrow\'s reality.  Find out more about the digital world of Siemens here: www.siemens.com/careers/digitalminds<br><br>PreSales Solutions Engineer - Mendix<br><br>As a PreSales Solutions Engineer (SE) on the Mendix PreSales team, you are a critical part of making the team successful.  You work with Sales and Solution Architects to build low-code apps that highlight our product value and key differentiators.  You work with customers and internal stakeholders to understand requirements and execute on those using your skills in system architecture and development.  <br><br>As a PreSales Solution Engineer with Mendix you are a "maker" who understands our customers.  You will be responsible for partnering with our Strategic Account Executives and Solution Architects to demonstrate the value of the Mendix platform.  Solution Engineers spend most of their time building with our low-code platform, and they combine this with customer-facing activities to support sales efforts.<br><br><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br><br>\u2022 Working with low-code tools to deliver POC apps to support the sales process<br><br>\u2022 Building process and infrastructure that supports the scalability of our presales team as it grows<br><br>\u2022 Facilitating discussions and workshops with customers to understand their application portfolio and find the best places for them to apply the Mendix Platform<br><br>\u2022 Performing product presentations and demonstrations (both online and onsite)<br><br>\u2022 Running technical deep dive and architecture sessions with customers, partners and other stakeholders<br><br>\u2022 Advising prospects and customers on the use of the Mendix Platform in their environment<br><br><strong>Required Skills:</strong><br><br>\u2022 Bachelor/MS degree in engineering, computer science, or equivalent degree in a technical field<br><br>\u2022 Over 5 years of recent fulltime (non-University-related) work experience. <br><br>\u2022 Must currently reside in the United States<br><br>\u2022 Recent experience developing with Java or other major programming language<br><br>\u2022 Good understanding of PaaS and the cloud market space<br><br>\u2022 Excellent communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to help customers find the right solution<br><br>\u2022 Can function independently in a fast-paced, dynamic work environment<br><br>\u2022 Comfortable presenting to all levels of an organization<br><br>\u2022 Open to 20% travel (based on pre-Covid travel expectations)<br><br>\u2022 Ability to work remotely<br><br>NOTE: Applicants will not require any type of employer sponsored work authorization now or in the future for employment in the USA. Applicants must be legally authorized for employment in the USA.<br><br><strong>Preferred Knowledge\\Skills, Education, and Experience:</strong><br><br>\u2022 Experience building apps with low-code platforms<br><br>\u2022 Experience with Siemens\' PLM portfolio, such as Teamcenter &amp; MindSphere<br><br>\u2022 Experience in a PreSales Solution Architect or Solution Engineer role <br><br>\u2022 Experience with Java, CSS, HTML, XML, SOAP, REST APIs and SQL<br><br>\u2022 Experience/training in solution selling<br><br>\u2022 Experience with Agile methodologies<br><br>#DISW<br><br>#LI-PLM<br><br>#LI-REMOTE<br><br>#LI-VS1<br><br><b>Organization:</b> Digital Industries<br><br><b>Company:</b> Siemens Industry Software Inc.<br><br><b>Experience Level:</b> Experienced Professional<br><br><b>Full / Part time:</b> Full-time<br><br><b>Equal Employment Opportunity Statement</b><br>Siemens is an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action Employer encouraging diversity in the workplace. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to their race, color, creed, religion, national origin, citizenship status, ancestry, sex, age, physical or mental disability unrelated to ability, marital status, family responsibilities, pregnancy, genetic information, sexual orientation, gender expression, gender identity, transgender, sex stereotyping, order of protection status, protected veteran or military status, or an unfavorable discharge from military service, and other categories protected by federal, state or local law.<br><br><b>EEO is the Law</b><br>Applicants and employees are protected under Federal law from discrimination. To learn more, Click here.<br><br><b>Pay Transparency Non-Discrimination Provision</b><br>Siemens follows Executive Order 11246, including the Pay Transparency Nondiscrimination Provision. To learn more, Click here.<br><br><b>California Privacy Notice</b><br>California residents have the right to receive additional notices about their personal information. To learn more, click here.</p>',
